                                                                                            <p><strong>Anne O. Fisher</strong>&rsquo;s latest translation is Ksenia Buksha&rsquo;s novel <a href="http://www.phonememedia.org/the-freedom-factory/"><em>The Freedom Factory</em></a> (2018), published by Phoneme Media. With poet Derek Mong, Fisher co-translated <a href="https://www.worldliteraturetoday.org/2018/september/joyous-science-selected-poems-maxim-amelin-maxim-amelin"><em>The Joyous Science: Selected Poems of Maxim Amelin</em></a>, winner of the 2018 Cliff Becker Book Prize in Translation (four of Amelin&rsquo;s poems appeared in the <a href="https://www.worldliteraturetoday.org/2017/september/four-poems-maxim-amelin">September 2017 issue</a> of <em>WLT</em>). With bilingual writer Margarita Meklina, Fisher co-edited the folio <em>Life Stories, Death Sentences: Contemporary Russian-Language LGBTQ+ Writing</em>, forthcoming in <em>In Translation</em> in conjunction with Pride Month 2019.</p>

