              <li>
          <div><div>  <a href="/blog/translation/mirza-alakbar-sabir-azerbaijani-poet-satirist-translation-lala-mammadova" hreflang="en"><img loading="lazy" src="/sites/worldliteraturetoday.org/files/styles/medium_thumbnail/public/Mammadova-anchor.jpg?itok=pjCl4OXn" width="250" height="175" alt="Mirza Alakbar Sabir and the first issue of Molla Nasreddin " typeof="foaf:Image" class="img-fluid image-style-medium-thumbnail" />

</a>

</div></div><div class="views-field views-field-field-richtitle"><p class="field-content"><a href="https://worldliteraturetoday.org/blog/translation/mirza-alakbar-sabir-azerbaijani-poet-satirist-translation-lala-mammadova">Mirza Alakbar Sabir: An Azerbaijani Poet-Satirist in Translation</a>
</p></div><div class="views-field views-field-field-author"><span class="views-label views-label-field-author field-name-field-blogauthor">By</span><span class="field-content field-name-field-blogauthor"><a href="/author/lala-mammadova" hreflang="en">Lala Mammadova</a>
</span></div>
        </li>
              <li>
          <div><div>  <a href="/blog/translation/translating-ecology-and-identity-how-wolf-totem-became-global-environmental" hreflang="en"><img loading="lazy" src="/sites/worldliteraturetoday.org/files/styles/medium_thumbnail/public/Pi-anchor.jpg?itok=M6B0s8Yc" width="250" height="175" alt="A collage of Wolf Totem book covers in translation" typeof="foaf:Image" class="img-fluid image-style-medium-thumbnail" />

</a>

