</div></div><div class="views-field views-field-field-thumbnail"><div class="field-content imageleft">  <a href="/blog/translation/mirza-alakbar-sabir-azerbaijani-poet-satirist-translation-lala-mammadova" hreflang="en"><img loading="lazy" src="/sites/worldliteraturetoday.org/files/styles/blog_thumbnail/public/Mammadova-anchor.jpg?itok=EGVDo0Cb" width="100" height="75" alt="Mirza Alakbar Sabir and the first issue of Molla Nasreddin " typeof="foaf:Image" class="img-fluid image-style-blog-thumbnail" />

</a>

</div></div><div class="views-field views-field-field-richtitle"><h4 class="field-content"><a href="https://worldliteraturetoday.org/blog/translation/mirza-alakbar-sabir-azerbaijani-poet-satirist-translation-lala-mammadova">Mirza Alakbar Sabir: An Azerbaijani Poet-Satirist in Translation</a>
</h4></div><div><div class="blog-summary">

Mirza Alakbar Sabir and the first issue of <em>Molla Nasreddin</em> / Photo courtesy of&nbsp;Wikipedia

The satirist and poet Mirza Alakbar Sabir (…
